description.narrative: ACO Supply and Logistics Section has been a front-line responder to various emergencies along with implementation of the regular Supply plan activities. The increased supply requirements, especially for L3 emergency response after August, have been procured and distributed supported by Supply Division, Regional and neighbouring country offices. In 2021, total procurement performed by the office reached $49,6M whereas $9.3M for goods and $40.3M for service contracting. Total supplies and services received including offshore procurement reached $128.97M and total supplies managed in CO&39;s controlled warehouses reached $35.85M | Status:On-track | As-of Date:12/01/2022
